'''Riccardo Berardino''' (born 12 October 1990) is an [[Football in Italy|Italian professional footballer]].
==Biography==
Born in [[Andria]], Apulia region, Berardino started his career at [[Vultur Rionero]], a local team in [[Eccellenza Basilicata]] (Italian sixth level until 2014). In 2008–09 season Berardino was signed by Abruzzo club [[Santegidiese Calcio S.S.D.|Santegidiese]] for [[2008–09 Serie D]]. (Italian fifth level until 2014) He moved further North for Marche club [[S.S. Real Montecchio|Real Montecchio]] in [[2009–10 Serie D]], however in November 2009 Berardino returned to [[Sant'Egidio alla Vibrata]].

In 2010 Berardino was signed by [[Lega Pro Seconda Divisione]] club [[S.S. Chieti Calcio|Chieti]]. The club entered 2012 promotion playoffs, losing to [[Paganese Calcio 1926|Paganese]]. Berardino was the starting attacking midfielder in 4–2–3–1 formation, after the suspension of [[Giuseppe Lacarra]];<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/523-chieti-aprilia-1-1-a-sabbatini-risponde-germani-la-finale-e-chieti-paganese.html|title=Chieti-Aprilia 1-1: a Sabbatini risponde Germani. La finale è Chieti-Paganese!|date=27 May 2012|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425023410/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/523-chieti-aprilia-1-1-a-sabbatini-risponde-germani-la-finale-e-chieti-paganese.html|archivedate=25 April 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/532-paganese-chieti-2-0-ko-pesante-ma-ora-tutti-uniti-a-caccia-dellimpresa.html|title=Paganese-Chieti 2-0: ko pesante ma ora tutti uniti a caccia dell'impresa!|date=3 June 2012|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425023415/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/532-paganese-chieti-2-0-ko-pesante-ma-ora-tutti-uniti-a-caccia-dellimpresa.html|archivedate=25 April 2014|df=}}</ref> in the first game Berardino was the substitute of [[Jonatan Alessandro]];<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/511-aprilia-chieti-2-2-pari-spettacolo-con-eurogol-di-del-pinto-appuntamento-a-domenica-prossima-allangelini.html|title=Aprilia - Chieti 2-2: pari spettacolo con eurogol di Del Pinto, appuntamento a domenica prossima!|date=20 May 2012|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425023331/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/511-aprilia-chieti-2-2-pari-spettacolo-con-eurogol-di-del-pinto-appuntamento-a-domenica-prossima-allangelini.html|archivedate=25 April 2014|df=}}</ref> Berardino replaced [[Lorenzo Del Pinto]] in the second half of the last game.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/544-chieti-paganese-0-0-il-bunker-campano-regge-solo-tanti-applausi-per-i-neroverdi.html|title=Chieti - Paganese 0-0: il bunker campano regge, solo tanti applausi per i neroverdi|date=10 June 2012|accessdate=22 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425024536/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/544-chieti-paganese-0-0-il-bunker-campano-regge-solo-tanti-applausi-per-i-neroverdi.html|archivedate=25 April 2014|df=}}</ref>

In summer 2012 Berardino left for fellow Abruzzo club [[S.S. Teramo Calcio|Teramo]]. On 31 January 2013 he returned to [[Chieti]] as free agent.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.teramocalcio.net/news.php?idnews=1158&idsezione=5|title=Risolto il rapporto con Berardino.|date=c.22 November 2012|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=SS Teramo Calcio|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/874-chiusa-la-finestra-di-calciomercato-giuseppe-colantoni-e-ricky-berardino-al-chieti.html|title=Chiusa la finestra di calciomercato: Giuseppe Colantoni e Ricky Berardino al Chieti!|date=31 January 2013|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427185807/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/874-chiusa-la-finestra-di-calciomercato-giuseppe-colantoni-e-ricky-berardino-al-chieti.html|archivedate=27 April 2014|df=}}</ref> Despite both clubs were in [[2012–13 Lega Pro Seconda Divisione]], Berardino only played 4 times in regular season, all for Chieti. In the playoffs Berardino was the substitute of Alessandro and starting attacking midfielder in 4-3-1-2 formation respectively. The club lost to [[L'Aquila Calcio 1927|L'Aquila]] in the first round,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/1032-laquila-chieti-2-0-episodi-determinanti-domenica-prossima-serve-limpresa.html|title=L'Aquila - Chieti 2-0: episodi determinanti, tra sette giorni serve l'impresa|date=26 May 2013|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427185804/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/1032-laquila-chieti-2-0-episodi-determinanti-domenica-prossima-serve-limpresa.html|archivedate=27 April 2014|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/1046-chieti-laquila-1-0-la-vittoria-piu-triste-in-finale-ci-vanno-i-rossoblu.html|title=Chieti - L'Aquila 1-0: la vittoria più triste, in finale ci vanno i rossoblu|date=2 June 2013|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=Chieti Calcio|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427190625/http://www.chieticalcio.com/nuovosito/index.php/archivio-news/1046-chieti-laquila-1-0-la-vittoria-piu-triste-in-finale-ci-vanno-i-rossoblu.html|archivedate=27 April 2014|df=}}</ref> which eventually L'Aquila was the winner.

